// Gauntlet Run 2.0 content: one NEW scenario (no base overrides) - a real
// parkour/slalom course. Spawns a player racer at the START, then guides the
// pilot gate by gate (objective + gold marker) through SIX gates to the
// FINISH, over three escalating acts (warmup / slalom / hazard). The route
// turns and climbs; invulnerable asteroids crowd the racing line to punish
// sloppy flying (collision damage), and an act-3 gravity well tugs the pilot
// off-line to sling or avoid. Crossing FINISH declares Victory; wrecking your
// ship on the rocks declares Defeat with a Retry. Pure flying skill, no combat.
// Data-driven RON (no engine changes); `base` is the only dependency - it owns
// the section prototypes the racer is built from and the shared textures. The
// racer's crash tolerance is base's reinforced_hull_section (200 health); it is
// tuned by playtest against that base value, NOT by any mod's overlay of that
// section (an enabled overlay could buff it, but gauntlet depends only on base).
//
// INVARIANT 1 (gate areas must not overlap): a `gate` counter (1..=7) gates
// each area's OnEnter, so the gates must be threaded IN ORDER; advancing `gate`
// only arms the NEXT gate's handler - the pilot still has to produce a fresh
// OnEnter on that area. If two gate areas overlapped, a pilot already loitering
// inside the next area when it went live would get no re-enter event and the
// race would soft-lock. Gates here sit 81-102u apart with 16-28u area radii, so
// this holds (min pairwise area gap ~36u); the gauntlet_course rig asserts
// pairwise non-overlap - keep it green when repositioning gates.
//
// INVARIANT 2 (the racing line stays flyable): every asteroid's WORST-CASE body
// (nominal radius * ASTEROID_GEOMETRIC_FACTOR_MAX = 6.0x - noise displaces the
// mesh far past its nominal radius; shakedown_run soft-locked a beat on exactly
// this) must clear the straight START->gate->...->FINISH polyline by a ship's
// margin. The autopilot GOTO flies that line, so a clear line means no
// soft-lock; rocks flank the line (the tightest ~9u past the ship margin), so
// the ideal line is safe but a wide, sloppy turn clips a rock. The rig measures
// this gap for every rock and the scatter field against the whole 3.5-6.0
// factor range - do not eyeball it. (Playtest may want the rocks pulled tighter
// to the line to bite harder; that is a feel pass, not a correctness change.)
[
    Scenario((
        id: "gauntlet_run",
        name: "Gauntlet Run",
        description: "A parkour course: thread six gates through asteroid slaloms and a gravity well, START to FINISH. Fly clean or wreck.",
        cubemap: "dep://base/textures/cubemap.png",
        // A 2D image: a UI thumbnail must NOT be the skybox cubemap (that Image
        // is reinterpreted to a Cube texture, which the UI pipeline cannot bind).
        thumbnail: Some("dep://base/textures/asteroid.png"),
        events: [
            (
                name: OnStart,
                filters: [],
                actions: [
                    DebugMessage((
                        message: "Gauntlet Run 2.0 loaded from the mod portal.",
                    )),
                    // The racer. Same section layout as the base player ship,
                    // with all verbs enabled (no DisableVerb): the pilot can
                    // GOTO/lock the gates from the first second. The reinforced
                    // hull buys crash tolerance so the course is run-and-fail,
                    // not one-touch death.
                    SpawnScenarioObject((
                        base: (
